Matches free-text requests against the STATUS.md task table, returning either a formatted row or the raw request as fallback. Matching is case-insensitive substring on the task column: exactly one match yields a formatted TASK ITEM, multiple matches error with all candidates listed, zero matches return the request unchanged.

The table model and parser are shared with `ctx-status` via [`ctx_core::status_table`]; changes to `Row` fields or parsing logic affect both crates. The three entry points are `resolve(status, request) -> Result<String, BriefError>`, which performs the full matching logic and returns the item or `AmbiguousItem` error, and `matched(status, request) -> bool`, which tells a genuine match from the no-match fallback without re-deriving the substring rule. Pipes in task cells are escaped with backslash in the markdown source and survive unescaped in matching.